<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2259] Spark submit documentation for --deploy-mode is highly misleading</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2259</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a few issues:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Client mode does not necessarily mean the driver program must be launched outside of the cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. For standalone clusters, only client mode is currently supported. This was the case supported even before 1.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, the docs tell the user to use cluster deploy mode when deploying &quot;your driver program within the cluster,&quot; which is true also for standalone-client mode. In short, the docs encourage the user to use standalone-cluster, an unsupported mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
